Header for handling UNIX terminal colors
C and C++ compatible

Copyright (C) 2010 Romain Porte
This header is under GPL ( for more info see the COPYING file )
     
 _  _ ___ __ _ __ _ ___ 
| || (_-</ _` / _` / -_)
 \_,_/__/\__,_\__, \___|
              |___/     

First don't forget to include the header file :

 #include "termcolor.h"

or

 #include <termcolor.h>

Then here's a green hello world :

C
-

printf("%sHello world%s\n", TC_Green, TC_Default);

C++
---

std::cout << TC_Green << "Hello world" << TC_Default << std::endl;

